SIMPLE: interlocution
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Interlocution
<hw>In`ter*lo*cu"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>interlocutio</ets>, from <ets>interloqui</ets>,
<ets>interlocutus</ets>, to speak between; <ets>inter</ets> between +
<ets>loqui</ets> to speak: cf. F. <ets>interlocution</ets>. See
<er>Loquacious</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Interchange of speech; dialogue; conversation;
conference.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>An intermediate act or decree
before final decision.</def> <rj><au>Ayliffe.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Hence, intermediate argument or
discussion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Interlocutor</ent>⟦br⟧
